UPDATING FIRMWARE

On Rev Hardware Client
1. Run Rev Hardware Client
2. Click Update Rev Hardware Client, if necessary

Drive NEO (Larger)
1. Plug Laptop into NEO motor
- Choose motor controller to update
2. Restore factory defaults (button at buttom of Basic tab)
3. Perform update, if necessary
4. Smart current limit 40
5. Set CAN ID
6. Click Persist Parameters (buttom at bottom)

Angle NEO (Small)
1. Plug laptop into Spark MAX motor controller
2. Restore factory default on Basic tab
3. Update Firmware, if necessary 
4. Set CAN ID
5. Smart Current limit 20 
6. Click Persist Parameters
7. Label Spark Max with CAN ID and Position

Through bore encoder
1. Connect encoder cable from turning motor to SPARK MAX
2. Attach breakout board to top of controller 
3. Connect 6 color ribbon cable between turning motor and breakout board
4. Rotate wheel close to zero 
5. Attach Calibration Plate
6. In Rev Hardware Client
- Go to absolute encoder tab
- Set direction = Inverted
- Click Zero Offset